main event: A civilian witness observed an unidentified object in December 1966 in Brandon, Florida.
interesting points: The object appeared as a nebulous hazy mass with no discernible contours., The object was copper colored with a dull finish and did not produce any trail or sound., The object was compared in size to a two-engine aircraft., The observation lasted about a minute before the object disappeared behind a cloud and did not reappear., The witness has training in aircraft recognition, adding credibility to the sighting.
sighted object: an unidentified copper-colored object resembling a hat
witness description: Mrs. J., a civilian with training in aircraft recognition
